Yes- Bug introduced via TSLint v5.13.0

### Description
All TSLint formatters now require that the linted file names be passed. This causes this line in devkit/build_angular/src/tslint/index to fail when using the checkstyle formatter (and likely others).
```
        if (!options.silent) {
          const Formatter = projectTslint.findFormatter(options.format);
          if (!Formatter) {
            throw new Error(`Invalid lint format "${options.format}".`);
          }
          const formatter = new Formatter();

          // FAILURE IS HERE.
          const output = formatter.format(result.failures, result.fixes);
          if(options.out) {

          }
          if (output) {
            this.context.logger.info(output);
          }
        }
```
Commit: https://github.com/palantir/tslint/commit/9000479b69c1f4808acf1dee284b47fbbbfbef13

## üî¨ Minimal Reproduction
In a current angular project, upgrade to `tslint v5.13.x`. Then run `ng lint --format=checkstyle`

